history.content:
Prob not. Key things:

-Make sure to have taken core classes for field

-Take some in what area you think you might be leaning towards within that to show interest

-Maybe a grad class or two

-RESEARCH!!!!!!!!! They generally say 2 years worth. Plus this can easily get you your 3 letters of rec

If you are on track for all this stuff before you have to start applying, I wouldn't worry, especially if you've been doing research

I was wondering if taking two technical classes only affects grad school/masters program admission. I'm currently at 18 units right now, taking 3 technicals classes, but I think another commitment will take me too much time so I am thinking of dropping one class. I will have 14 units(8 graded) by the end of the drop. Is there a chance that this affects admissions?

history.content: I'm a second year right now, and I was wondering if taking two technical classes only affects grad school/master program prospects. I'm currently at 18 units right now, taking 3 technicals classes, but I think research will take me too much time so I am thinking of dropping one class with the late drop. I will have 14 units by the end of the drop. So only 8 units on my transcript will be graded units. Is there a chance that this looks bad? I haven't fully decided dropping the particular class, but I am using my late action and I have to decide asap in which way I will use it. Furthermore these two classes I would remain in are lower divs, as I'm dropping my upper div. My other units are AI and a DeCal (so I'm not taking a third elective or anything)
